Body (Fig. 11), especially elytra, rather flat, 7.4-8.4 mm in length. DMF very wide (Fig. 6), outwardly extended to interval 9, PAS fairly short and transverse; PHSe short, expanded to interval 5 posteriorly and mostly also to interval 7 anteriorly, PHSi small, occupying intervals 3 and 4 posterior to PHSe, sometimes almost isolated. DSS transverse, mostly subangulate posterolaterally. Underside dark, middle of prosternum, meso- and metaventrite, as well as a narrow apical margin of abdominal sternite VII pale; 
outer
half of metacoxae infuscate. Microsculpture coarse on elytra, obliterate on both pronotum and back half of head, with almost indistinct traces here and there on pronotal disc.
